Content: [dscrd-hush] <anglersec> Ok.  So in a nutshell what caused Hush to drop from a high of $26 to ten cents?  Are there specific reasons?  Please dont flame.  Honestly wanting to know

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <halo kitty rules> @anglersec First reason is 2017 altcoin rally, combined with expectations of BTCH airdrop. Price was overhyped. Second reason is switching from GPU to ASIC mining. Newly generated coins are ÀùmintedÀù cheaper.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <anglersec> @halo kitty rules Many thanks for the explanation.  Completely understand the price overhype.  So moving to ASIC mining. How much cheaper are the coins minted.  Trying to determine realistic target price for Hush as BTC approaches ATH....

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <halo kitty rules> Price of GPU coins was for a long time about 1 USD. At the break of 2018/2019 were ASIC coins sold at 0.03 or 0.05 USD. Now it is about 0.10 USD. Let say fair price is 0.05-0.10 USD and miner still make some profit.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> @anglersec it's a fair question, we are friendly to fair questions üòÉ
